    getUnique

    getUnique.Rd

    getUnique

    Usage

    getUnique(.data)

    Arguments

    .data

    input data as used in a pipe

    Value

    Dataframe where the rows are the columns of .data. For each variable the function returns the number of unique values, nu_unique, and what these values are, unique_values. NOTE: Columns that are constant are not shown.

    Examples

    data(mtcars)
mtcars %>% getUnique()
